title: Appointments to the Health and Medical Development Advisory Committee
content_text:
p>
The Government today (February 27) announced the reappointment of Mr Ronald 
Joseph Arculli as the Vice-Chairman of the Health and Medical Development 
Advisory Committee (HMDAC).  Ten serving non-official members were also reappointed and three new 
non-official members were appointed. All the appointments are for a term of 
two years with effect from March 1, 2009. The Secretary for Food and Health and the Chairman of the committee, Dr York 
Chow, welcomed the new members to the committee. They are Professor Sophie

Chow, welcomed the new members to the committee. They are Professor Sophie 
Chan Siu-chee, Dr Sigmund Leung Sai-man and Mr James Wong Ngar-kok. Following is a brief biography of the three new members: Professor Sophie Chan is the Head of the Department of Nursing Studies at 
the University of Hong Kong. She is also a member of the Nursing Council of 
Hong Kong. Professor Chan has rich experience in nurse training and she is 
active in promoting the development of the nursing profession with the aim

active in promoting the development of the nursing profession with the aim 
of improving the nursing service in Hong Kong.  Dr Leung is the President of Hong Kong Dental Association. As an experienced 
dentist, he is enthusiastic in promoting dental health and the professional 
development of dentists in Hong Kong. Mr James Wong Ngar-kok is the Honorary Professor of both the School of 
Chinese Medicine of the University of Hong Kong, and the School of Chinese 
Medicine of the Hong Kong Baptist University. He is also a member of the

Medicine of the Hong Kong Baptist University. He is also a member of the Chinese Medicine Council of Hong Kong. Mr Wong is actively involved in promoting the development of traditional Chinese medicine in Hong Kong. The re-appointed members are: Mr Chan Kin-por

Dr Loretta Yam Yin-chun A spokesman for the Food and Health Bureau said: "Following the completion of the first stage public consultation on healthcare reform in June last year, we are now working on the implementation of various service reform proposals, which have been well-received by the public, and development of

proposals, which have been well-received by the public, and development of 
detailed financing proposals for the second stage public consultation. "Given the major role that the private medical sector plays in Hong Kong's 
healthcare system, we would like to invite professionals from more 
healthcare sub-sectors so as to broaden the advisory base for the service 
reform implementation and the second stage public consultation." The HMDAC is tasked to review and develop the service model for healthcare 
in both the public and private sectors, and propose long-term healthcare

in both the public and private sectors, and propose long-term healthcare financing options. Following is the membership list of the committee from March 1: Chairman: Dr York Chow, the Secretary for Food and Health Vice-chairman: Mr Ronald Joseph Arculli Non-official members:
